                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Hand a: Mediocre but careful; hand b: mediocre,
                           irregular; hand c: mediocre; hand d: careful.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red (vivid red, reddish-brown)</seg>
                        Scribe: Ṣǝge Mikāʾel. Ṣǝge Mikāʾel
                        is mentioned as the scribe for Text I (s. <locus target="#18va">18va</locus>).<date>18th century (?)</date>
                        <list type="abbreviations">
                           <item>ይካ፡ for ይብል፡ ካህን፡</item>
                           <item>ይዲ፡ for ይብል፡ ዲያቆን፡</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; incipit of Text I; name of the scribe;
                           name of the donor; directive to the minister and their abbreviations; the
                           word ʾǝgäle; initial line of the prayers; titles of the books to be read;
                           element of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals.
 On
                           the incipit page of Text I (fol. 1r, few lines are rubricated
                           (alternating witn black lines).</seg>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">Hand a: <locus from="1ra" to="18va">1ra-18va</locus>,
                        27ra-28vb.</handNote>
